---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research Facility | EES"
  description="Our purpose-built TestCell for real-world thermal comfort and energy efficiency testing, equipped to ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 standards."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Research Facility</h1>
      <p>Purpose-built for real-world thermal comfort and energy testing.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>The TestCell</h2>
      <p>
        We built a full-scale test cell to develop and validate our products under real conditions — not just in theory.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our TestCell is a real room (3.6m × 4.8m × 3.0m high) constructed to Australian Standard specifications with R2.0 batt insulation. It features a 7.5m² clear double-glazed, north-facing glass unit to commercial grade — designed to simulate worst-case solar gain.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Measure</h2>
      <p>
        The TestCell is equipped with professional-grade instrumentation aligned to international comfort and performance standards:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>ASHRAE-55 / ISO 7730 Comfort Carts</strong> — measuring operative temperature and thermal comfort</li>
        <li><strong>Heat Flux Meters</strong> — quantifying radiant and conductive energy transfer through surfaces</li>
        <li><strong>Air Velocity Metering</strong> — tracking airflow patterns within the space</li>
        <li><strong>Air Temperature Stratification Strings</strong> — mapping temperature differences from floor to ceiling</li>
        <li><strong>Ventilation Air Change Rate Monitoring</strong> — verifying fresh air delivery and infiltration</li>
        <li><strong>Thermal Imaging Cameras</strong> — visualising surface temperatures and identifying heat loss</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <p>We use the TestCell for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full thermal comfort evaluation of our products (heating and cooling)</li>
        <li>Energy efficiency benchmarking under controlled and real-world conditions</li>
        <li>Development and tuning of control systems</li>
        <li>Independent third-party testing for external clients</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Interested in third-party testing? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> for more information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
